(466, 1, '2014-02-10 11:48:36', '2014-02-10 04:48:36', 'Manado  The Indonesian Banks Association (PERBANAS) and the Humanitarian Banking Society Committee (KMPP), Monday (10/2) provided disaster relief to natural disaster victims in the village of Pinaesaan, Manado. The relief was given by the Head of PERBANAS Regional Branch in North Sulawesi, Ferry A. Keintjem accompanied by Luctor Tapiheru.\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\nPrior to distributing it to the victims, the relief was officially handed to the Mayor of Manado, G.S. Vicky Lumentul represented by Deputy Mayor Harley A.B. Mangindaan.\r\n\r\nOn behalf of the Mayor, the Manado City Government, and the people of Manado, especially those who are affected by the natural disaster on 15 January, I would like to thank Perbanas who has shown sympathy and compassion towards the disaster victims. This relief has also encouraged us to continue helping the victims, said Mangindaan, regularly knows as Ai.\r\n\r\nOn a different note, Ai also informed the people of Manado about the working plans of the Manado City Government, who in the next 3 weeks will conduct a total cleanup of all areas including clogged drainage.\r\n\r\nThe Mayor and I hope that through this relief, the people of Manado will be stronger in facing disasters and work together to recover the city of Manado, he added.\r\n\r\nIn total, PERBANAS and KMPP donated 20 units of water pumps, 200 gas cylinders each weighing 3kg and 1600 items of clothing. Donations from PERBANAS and KMPP will be sent to several different regions affected by the disaster in Manado. (manatoday.com)\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Manado City Government Receives Disaster Relief from PERBANAS', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'manado-city-government-of-perbanas-receive-disaster-assistance', '', '', '2014-06-24 07:58:16', '2014-06-24 00:58:16', '', 0, 'http://perbanas.org/beta/en/?post_type=news&#038;p=466', 0, 'news', '', 0),
(467, 1, '2014-06-12 11:48:36', '2014-06-12 04:48:36', 'SATURN - Union National Bank (PERBANAS) and the Committee on Banking Community Care (KMPP), Monday (10/2) to provide assistance to disaster victims in the Village Pinaesaan, Manado, which is delivered directly PERBANAS Chairman of North Sulawesi, Ferry A Keintjem accompanied Luctor Tapiheru.\r\n\r\nBefore submitted directly to the rock community received the Mayor of Manado, GS Lumentut represented by Vice Mayor Vicky Harley Manado AB Mangindaan.\r\n\r\n"I represent the Mayor, Board of Manado City Government, and all citizens of the city of Manado, more specifically affected January 15 thank Perbanas who have shown sympathy and concern for the victims of the disaster. This assistance also continues to encourage us all tirelessly to help the victims, "said Ai Mangindaan familiar greeting.\r\n\r\nOn the same occasion, Vice Mayor Pinaesaan inform residents about the concept of Manado City Government employment in the next 3 weeks will melaksakana in all lines including cleaning clogged drainage evenly.\r\n\r\n"I hope the mayor and the citizens through the help we received is then channeled to more robust in the face of disaster and help each other help to restore the city of Manado," said Dr.. Harley.\r\n\r\nAs is known, PERBANAS and KMPP added 20 units of machinery Alkon, 200 gas cylinder 3kg and 1600 pieces of clothing. Assistance from KMPP PERBANAS and will be distributed in various areas of Manado City disaster site. (Manadotoday.com)', 'Manado City Government of PERBANAS Receive Disaster Assistance', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '466-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-06-12 11:48:36', '2014-06-12 04:48:36', '', 466, 'http://perbanas.org/beta/en/466-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
