(1077, 1, '2014-06-20 15:43:10', '2014-06-20 08:43:10', 'The banking industry is constantly evolving to keep in line with the overall economy. PERBANAS as an organization for banks in Indonesia must also be able to evolve dynamically over time. It aims to broaden the knowledge of its members in the midst of rapid progress in all fields.\r\n\r\nPERBANAS is currently an open organization, its members not only consisting of national private banks as at the beginning of its establishment, but also accepting other types of banks such as state owned banks and Regional Development Banks (BPD). The decision for an open organization was achieved during the 15th financial industry. Congress which was held in Jakarta in 2003, taking into account the developments of the\r\n\r\nWith open membership, PERBANAS is expected to be the only organization in the banking industry, thus making the banking sector increasingly solid in anticipation of problems that may occur now or in the future. This matter is also in accordance to the wishes of the government that there shall not be too many banking organizations in Indonesia.\r\n<h2>Committee Structure</h2>\r\n<p class="text-center in-article-diagram"><a href="http://perbanas.org/beta/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/PBS_Website_LO4_About-StructCom01.gif"><img class="img-responsive" src="http://perbanas.org/beta/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/PBS_Website_LO4_About-StructCom01.gif" alt="[cml_media_alt id=''1024'']PBS_Website_LO4_About-StructCom01[/cml_media_alt]" width="1000" height="1597" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>CSR / KMPP</h2>\r\n<p class="last">As an act of its corporate social responsibilty (CSR), Perbanas formed Komite Masyarakat Perbankan Peduli (KMPP) or also called Perbanas Peduli on 14 June 2006. The main goal of KMPP is to give aid to victims of natural disasters.\r\nThe vision and mission of KMPP is none other than an act of compassion from the PERBANAS banking community in Indonesia to those who have been devastated by a natural disaster. Therefore during the last few years, all of the members of Perbanas have collectively been committed to implement CSR programs which have a national impact, especially in the field of education.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>PROGRAM OF ACTIVITIES</h2>\r\n<h3>Fixed Program</h3>\r\nReconstruction/renovation of school buildings (elementary) which have been destroyed.\r\n<h3>Short Term Program</h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><i>Banking Education</i>. Provide educational banking seminars for teachers and students. As a first step, will be implemented at 5 schools which were built by KMPP, which are: SDN Giwangan-Yogya, SDN Kabregan-Bantul, SDN Kotesan-Klaten, SDN Panjalu-Ciamis, and SDN Ngadirejo-Bromo.</li>\r\n	<li><i>Training for Trainers</i>. Provide training for talented individuals to become trainers.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3>National Disaster Relief</h3>\r\n1. Fulfilling the needs of disaster victims\r\n\r\n2. Post disaster relief\r\n<h3>Mid Term Program</h3>\r\n1. Provide courses and teach skills in a certain field to communities who need it in order to start a business. Example: cooking, making batik, reflexology, hairdressing or herbal medicine.\r\n\r\n2. Create economically independent villages with one basic form of business. Example: An economically independent village with herbal medicine as its main business.', 'What We Do', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '417-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-06-20 15:43:10', '2014-06-20 08:43:10', '', 417, 'http://perbanas.org/beta/en/417-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1078, 1, '2014-06-20 15:46:05', '2014-06-20 08:46:05', 'Industri perbankan terus mengalami perkembangan seiring dengan pembaharuan ekonomi secara keseluruhan. PERBANAS sebagai wadah untuk bank-bank di Indonesia juga harus terus mengembangkan diri secara dinamis seiring berjalannya waktu. Tujuan utamanya adalah untuk memperluas wawasan dan pengetahuan anggotanya ditengah-tengah kemajuan dalam segala sektor.\r\n\r\nPERBANAS saat ini merupakan organisasi terbuka, anggotanya tidak hanya terdiri dari bank-bank nasional swasta seperti pada saat pendiriannya, namun juga telah menerima jenis bank lainnya seperti Bank BUMN dan Bank Pembangunan Daerah (BPD). Keputusan untuk menjadi organisasi terbuka ditetapkan dalam Kongres XV yang diselenggarakan di Jakarta pada tahun 2003, dengan pertimbangan berbagai perkembangan yang tengah terjadi pada industri perbankan.\r\n\r\nDengan keanggotaan yang terbuka, PERBANAS diharapkan menjadi satu-satunya organisasi dalam industri perbankan sehingga dapat mempererat sektor ini dalam mengantisipasi berbagai kendala yang mungkin dihadapi kedepannya. Selain itu, juga seiring dengan keinginan pemerintah agar tidak terdapat terlalu banyak organisasi perbankan di Indonesia.\r\n\r\n<h2>Struktur Komite</h2>\r\n<p class="text-center in-article-diagram"><a href="http://perbanas.org/beta/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/PBS_Website_LO4_About-StructCom01.gif"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1024" src="http://perbanas.org/beta/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/PBS_Website_LO4_About-StructCom01.gif" alt="[cml_media_alt id=''1024'']PBS_Website_LO4_About-StructCom01[/cml_media_alt]" width="1000" height="1597" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>CSR / KMPP</h2>\r\nSebagai bentuk corporate social responsibility (CSR), Perbanas membentuk Komite Masyarakat Perbankan Peduli (KMPP) atau disebut juga Perbanas Peduli pada tanggal 14 Juni 2006. Tujuan utama KMPP adalah untuk memberikan bantuan kepada para korban yang terkena bencana alam.\r\nAdapun visi dan misi KMPP, yaitu sebagai bentuk kepedulian masyarakat perbankan Indonesia PERBANAS kepada mereka yang tertimpa musibah bencana alam, maka seluruh anggota Perbanas secara kolektif selama beberapa tahun terakhir melalui wadahnya KMPP terus berkomitmen untuk menyelenggarakan program CSR yang mempunyai dampak nasional khususnya di bidang pendidikan.\r\n<h2>PROGRAM KERJA</h2>\r\n<h3>Program Tetap</h3>\r\nPembangunan kembali / renovasi bangunan sekolah (SD) yang rusak.\r\n<h3>Program Jangka Pendek</h3>\r\n1. <i>Banking Education</i>. Penyelenggaraan seminar edukasi perbankan untuk guru dan murid. Untuk langkah awal akan dimulai dari 5 sekolah yang telah dibangun oleh KMPP yaitu: SDN Giwangan-Yogya, SDN Kabregan-Bantul, SDN Kotesan-Klaten, SDN Panjalu-Ciamis, dan SDN Ngadirejo-Bromo.\r\n\r\n2. <i>Training for Trainers</i>. Memberikan pelatihan kepada orang yang berbakat untuk menjadi trainer.\r\n<h3>Bantuan Bencana Nasional</h3>\r\n1. Bantuan kebutuhan korban bencana\r\n\r\n2. Bantuan pasca bencana\r\n<h3>Program Menengah</h3>\r\n1. Kewirausahaan dan Keterampilan : Memberikan kursus dan keterampilan di bidang tertentu kepada masyarakat yang membutuhkan untuk bekal berwirausaha. Misalnya: memasak, membatik, refleksi, salon, usaha jamu.\r\n\r\n2. Desa Swadaya Ekonomi : Membentuk desa swadaya ekonomi dengan berbasis suatu model tertentu. Misalnya Desa Swadaya Ekonomi yang berbasis usaha jamu.', 'Kegiatan Perbanas', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '903-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-06-20 15:46:05', '2014-06-20 08:46:05', '', 903, 'http://perbanas.org/beta/en/903-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1079, 1, '2014-06-20 15:52:54', '2014-06-20 08:52:54', 'The banking industry is constantly evolving to keep in line with the overall economy. PERBANAS as an organization for banks in Indonesia must also be able to evolve dynamically over time. It aims to broaden the knowledge of its members in the midst of rapid progress in all fields.\r\n\r\nPERBANAS is currently an open organization, its members not only consisting of national private banks as at the beginning of its establishment, but also accepting other types of banks such as state owned banks and Regional Development Banks (BPD). The decision for an open organization was achieved during the 15th financial industry. Congress which was held in Jakarta in 2003, taking into account the developments of the\r\n\r\n<p class="last">With open membership, PERBANAS is expected to be the only organization in the banking industry, thus making the banking sector increasingly solid in anticipation of problems that may occur now or in the future. This matter is also in accordance to the wishes of the government that there shall not be too many banking organizations in Indonesia.</p>\r\n<h2>Committee Structure</h2>\r\n<p class="text-center in-article-diagram"><a href="http://perbanas.org/beta/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/PBS_Website_LO4_About-StructCom01.gif"><img class="img-responsive" src="http://perbanas.org/beta/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/PBS_Website_LO4_About-StructCom01.gif" alt="[cml_media_alt id=''1024'']PBS_Website_LO4_About-StructCom01[/cml_media_alt]" width="1000" height="1597" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>CSR / KMPP</h2>\r\n<p class="last">As an act of its corporate social responsibilty (CSR), Perbanas formed Komite Masyarakat Perbankan Peduli (KMPP) or also called Perbanas Peduli on 14 June 2006. The main goal of KMPP is to give aid to victims of natural disasters.\r\nThe vision and mission of KMPP is none other than an act of compassion from the PERBANAS banking community in Indonesia to those who have been devastated by a natural disaster. Therefore during the last few years, all of the members of Perbanas have collectively been committed to implement CSR programs which have a national impact, especially in the field of education.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>PROGRAM OF ACTIVITIES</h2>\r\n<h3>Fixed Program</h3>\r\nReconstruction/renovation of school buildings (elementary) which have been destroyed.\r\n<h3>Short Term Program</h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><i>Banking Education</i>. Provide educational banking seminars for teachers and students. As a first step, will be implemented at 5 schools which were built by KMPP, which are: SDN Giwangan-Yogya, SDN Kabregan-Bantul, SDN Kotesan-Klaten, SDN Panjalu-Ciamis, and SDN Ngadirejo-Bromo.</li>\r\n	<li><i>Training for Trainers</i>. Provide training for talented individuals to become trainers.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3>National Disaster Relief</h3>\r\n1. Fulfilling the needs of disaster victims\r\n\r\n2. Post disaster relief\r\n<h3>Mid Term Program</h3>\r\n1. Provide courses and teach skills in a certain field to communities who need it in order to start a business. Example: cooking, making batik, reflexology, hairdressing or herbal medicine.\r\n\r\n2. Create economically independent villages with one basic form of business. Example: An economically independent village with herbal medicine as its main business.', 'What We Do', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '417-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-06-20 15:52:54', '2014-06-20 08:52:54', '', 417, 'http://perbanas.org/beta/en/417-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
