(1091, 1, '2014-06-23 09:36:12', '2014-06-23 02:36:12', 'Jakarta  The rapid development of technology in the information and communication sector, as well as globalization in the banking system, has made banks become main targets for money laundering. This is due to the fact that banks still play a strategic role in supporting the financial system in Indonesia.\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\nAlso, the strict confidentiality of banks is also one of the main considerations for money launderers.\r\n\r\nThus conveyed by banking law analyst, Pradjoto, in a seminar held by the Indonesia Banks Association (PERBANAS) themed Legal Review on the Role of Banks in Indonesia in Facing Money Laundering and Terrorism Funding, held in Jakarta, Thursday, 19 December 2013.\r\n\r\nAccording to Pradjoto, it is important to apply the principles of Know Your Customer (KYC) in every bank transaction. Also, there needs to be strong supervision and commitment from the banking board of directors and commissioners, as well as reports to the Financial Transaction Report and Analysis Center (PPATK), should there be any suspicious transactions.\r\n\r\nHead of PERBANAS Law Sector who is also Director of Compliance, Corporate Affairs &amp; Legal at PT Bank CIMB Niaga Tbk, L. Wulan Tumbaleka says, money laundering can now be done by anyone from all levels of society. The techniques used are also more advanced, therefore seeming more competitive with the eradication efforts done by law enforcers.\r\n\r\nPerbanas calls for the banking society as well as the general public to share their experiences and play an active role in overseeing financial transactions which can potentially be crimes of money laundering or terrorism funding, says Wulan.\r\n\r\nAs an organization for national banks in Indonesia, Perbanas, through its Law Sector, has given recommendations to the government in the drafting of Banking Laws, recommendations in general as well as specifically concerning money laundering. Direct recommendations from banking practitioners in Indonesia are important to achieve a Banking Law which is appropriate with the needs of the banking industry as well as stakeholders.\r\n\r\nAccording to Wulan, recommendations from Perbanas are based on proposals and ideas from national banks. Recommendations from Perbanas for the Banking Law have become a commitment for Perbanas in order to achieve a better future for the banking industry, closed Wulan. (infobanknews.com)\r\n\r\nAs an organization that embodies national banks in Indonesia, Perbanas, through Perbanas Legal Affairs, has provided input to the government in the preparation of the Act (the Act) Banking, both in general and with regard to the crime of money laundering. Direct input from the banking industry in Indonesia, it becomes important for the creation of the Banking Law that really fit the needs of the banking industry and stakeholders.\r\n\r\nInputs given Perbanas, according Wulan, or have previously been proposed based on the idea of national banks. "Inputs from Perbanas to be committed Perbanas Banking Act in order to bring the future of the banking industry better," Wulan lid. (Infobanknews.com)', 'Banks an Easy Target for Money Laundering', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '440-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-06-23 09:36:12', '2014-06-23 02:36:12', '', 440, 'http://perbanas.org/beta/en/440-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
